    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>FUEL SURCHARGE BY AIRLINES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's airlines are given government approval to raise fares on domestic flights by up to 19.03 percent to compensate for higher fuel prices (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's airlines have been given government approval to raise fares on domestic flights by up to 19.03 percent to compensate for higher fuel prices. The government increased the price of jet fuel by 34.5 percent last week. Varig, Brazil's largest carrier, has said it plans to increase fares by the full amount.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich</p>
      </block>
